I have uploaded 3 mask options to choose from (click "Action!" under the mask to select). 
Force rate at 0 it will be initial, at 12 it will accelerate and double the cycle.
In "Your Mask" you can upload yours.

From time to time I will post new masks here - https://titto13.imgur.com/all

Using the "Rotate Mask" function, you can play around by rotating the mask. The results of these actions can be seen in "Mask Frames"(IP). The on/off button is on the left. Stripes Mask: Great for this.
In "Mask Frames" you can see the approximate movements of the "Load White" and "Load Black" images. This makes it easier to control the final animation.

These are additional tools and tips, they are not required.
 
On the left (for White) and on the right (for Black) there are various image manipulations. You can see the results of these manipulations in "Preview White" and "Preview Black". 
Ill try to explain why this is needed and the general operating principles of IPAdapter. 

If the image is not square, IPAdapter will crop it to the center.
You can see what it looks like if you turn on "Fast Crop" and select the crop position "center". To prevent this from happening, there are two options: 
1. Upload square images. 
2. Enable "Fast Crop" with crop position "pad". It will make the image square by adding black stripes on the sides.

But if you don't need the whole image using "Fast Crop", you can select the area to crop it, or cut out a specific detail using "Detail Crop".

Image Rotate and Image Flip: I think its clear what they are doing. If it's not clear, turn it on and try.

All of this can give you more control over your animation creation.

Play around with "strength" from 0.4 to 1.0
              "end_percent" from 0.350 to 0.800
Sometimes you can turn it off and still get an interesting result (depending on the choice of mask). On/off button on the left.
Increasing this value provides more movement but reduces detail. I'm working in the range 1.000-1.300. But don't be afraid to experiment. If you want to throw a party, feel free to put 1.500))

https://huggingface.co/guoyww/animatediff/resolve/main/v3_sd15_adapter.ckpt?download=true

This creates smoother transitions and increases detail, but may reduce movement. Therefore, at 0.4 set the Motion Scale to 1.000-1.150, at 1.0 to 1.100-1.500. Can be disabled. Button on/off the left.

The length of my masks is 48 frames, if the force rate in the mask is set to 12, they are accelerated by 2 times. Therefore, if you want a very short animation, you can use 24 frames. Or vice versa longer for example 72.

https://github.com/cubiq/ComfyUI_IPAdapter_plus#installation

It is preferable to use the "VIT-G" preset, it gives more stable results.
If you want results that are closer to your images, switch to PLUS and change the weight_type to ease in-out.
